DESCRIPTION:Journey through Mulyana: Vital EcosystemsвҖ”an imaginative\, 
 immersive installation that transforms the museum into a vibrant\, handcr
 afted\, underwater ecosystem. Inspired by Indonesia's spectacular coral r
 eefs\, acclaimed fiber artist Mulyana (b. 1984\, Indonesia) has meticulou
 sly hand-knit and crocheted colorful coral reefs\, playful fish\, and fan
 tastical sea creaturesвҖ”while reflecting on how human wellness is interc
 onnected with the wellbeing of our oceans. Read more about this featured 
 exhibition. (https://artmuseum.indiana.edu/exhibitions/current/_feature-e
 xhibitions/2026-02-07-mulyana-vital-ecosystems.html)  Then step into the 
 world of acclaimed photographer Rania Matar (b. 1964\, Lebanon)\, whose s
 triking portraits document young women persisting in uncertain times. In 
 the exhibition Rania Matar: Where Do I Go?Щ„ЩҲЩҠЩҶШұЩҲШӯШҹ\, Matar's lens
  highlights women's creativity\, strength\, dignity\, and resilienceвҖ”of
 fering a powerful counter-narrative to the challenges of her country and 
 region. Read more about this featured exhibition (https://artmuseum.india
 na.edu/exhibitions/upcoming/_feature-exhibitions/2026-03-05-rania-matar-w
 here-do-i-go.html).  &#160\;  Know Before You GoSpace is available for th
 e first 12 people to check in with Guest Services on the day. Check in at
  the information desk on the first floor of the museum when you arrive.A 
 small handbag may be carried at your side. Backpacks and large bags will 
 need to be stored before touring. Learn more aboutmuseum guidelines.If yo
 u park in the IMU parking lot\, Guest Services can validate your parking 
 voucher for a discount.Read aboutwhere to find us and where to park\,
